name: Edwards Santa Maria 10 Cinemas

name: mcdonalds, 337 Mcmurray Rd,buelton, ca
comment: its a gender neutral ADA bathroom

name: University of Georgia, Main Library
street: Main Library (off of Jackson St. on UGA North Campus)
directions: There are two single-stall locking bathrooms in the basement in the periodicals area.

name: Cookies Cafe
directions: it's on the left side of the counter where the cookies are displayed.
comment: it has pretty nice tile.

name: SUNY Purchase
directions: Find Campus Center North (Just ask around) and walk in the main doors. Look to your left (across from the moore card office) and there is a gender free bathroom.
comment: Open 24 hours a day. Not the cleanest, but safe!

name: Keggers Ale House
directions: Back of the pub past the bar on the left. NOT GENDER NEUTRAL but - the men's room has stalls which walls go all the way from floor to ceiling and lock. not sure about womens.
comment: nice place to have a beer, good music.

name: Rhizome Cafe
directions: On the main floor in the back of the cafe. Two washrooms, both gn.

name: Mitzi's Cafe
directions: Back of the cafe - main floor.
comment: Owner is queer, staff are queer/friendly.

name: York University - Tel Building
directions: There are 2 on every floor, one near the elevators - the other i can't really describe.
comment: They actually put tranny friendly stickers onto the sign as well as the 'handicap' sign.

name: Second Cup
directions: Second Cup caf√© attached to Paragraphe. Requires a key though if someone has the key you may be able to duck in when they come out.

name: The Bowery Electric
directions: The bathrooms in the basement room (performance space and bar) are single-use and genderfree.
comment: As its a bar, it probably has late hours. Also, you may need ID showing that you are over 21.

name: Dalhousie University
directions: Two single occupancy bathrooms, labelled as bi-gender.  In the basement of the Computer Science Building on Dalhousie Campus, down the stairs and to the right.  (Left off the elevator), look for the signs.
comment: 8:30am to 5:00pm free access to the building.  Outside those hours, you must have University ID.Accessibility: Door width unknown, Lever handle, single door, there is space beside the toilet, and a grab bar, grab bar is on the left, toilet paper is above grab bar, flush is on wall side, there is no toilet seat cover dispenser, the sink is roll-under.  The door lock works.(Jan, 2010)For more Gender Neutral washrooms on Dal Campus, visit http://dalally.studentservices.dal.ca/Gender-Neutral_Washr.php

name: McGill University, Shatner Building
directions: 4th floor - the main stairs only go up to the 3rd floor, but there are signs that will direct you from there to the stairs to the 4th floor - there is also an elevator that will take you there

name: Taco Bell
street: 1 block north of Broadway and Littleton blvd.
directions: on the right as you first walk in

name: Barnes and Noble-- Boston Univ. Kenmore Square T-Stop
directions: 2nd Floor.
comment: Blend in with the students/shoppers

name: Starbucks
directions: around the corner near the front windows

name: Modesto/Chipotle
directions: There is a side door on the right right next to the bathrooms, can just walk right in and right back out.  The rooms are gendered, but it is easy to time a quick in and out without being seen.

name: subway
directions: in the back

name: Diamond Jim's Grill
comment: Tiny old-school diner, popular w/locals. Wait staff is down-to-earth.

name: Automatic Public Toilets Faneuil Hall
street: Congress Street at 1 City Hall Plaza
directions: Near Haymarket (on the Green/Orange subway lines) and State Steet Station (on the Blue/Orange subway lines)
comment: This is one of the pay toilets installed by the City.  They are non-gendered, but be prepared for the stares of tourists (who these toilets were intended for).Still, I've never had a problem with using them.  In the early evening, when there's not a lot of people waiting, 50 cents or a dollar will get you enough time to take a sponge bath in the sinks and get cleaned up if youre transient.

name: U of O Law School Library
directions: 2nd floor
comment: don't forget to knock first!

name: COSI Science Center
directions: All floors, all restrooms in building.
comment: At all restrooms in building, centered between separate M and F restrooms, there are "Family Restrooms" that are single stall, locking restrooms that can be used by anyone.

name: Austin Bergstrom International Airport
comment: Special Needs Bathroom, Single stall.  I've never been questioned going in.

name: City College
directions: Student Union, top floor.Cloud Hall, top floor.Rec Center, top floor.
comment: What is it about city college and gender neutral bathrooms on the top floor? The bathroom in cloud and the rec center are awesome.The one in the student union is simply the men's single stall with a new sign.  It is mostly men that use it.

name: McDonalds
directions: At back of dining room. There is a door from the outside facing the parking lot that opens right next to the restrooms. Should you not want to buy anything, it's possible to walk right in, then right back out again.
comment: This is the same McDonalds, I just found two different addresses for it.  It's the same road.  Take Todd Rd. exit from Hwy 29, turn East and you'll see it.  It's right off the freeway.  There is a traffic circle there, and it's safest to go all the way around the circle before turning into the McDonalds driveway.  Note that these are single stall gendered bathrooms in a small town.  I suggest using the one of the gender you are presenting as.

name: Lake County Career Center
directions: 1st floor, to the left of the Career Center entrance.
comment: 8am to 5pm, M-F.  The building is a little hard to find (in case you happen to be vacationing on Clear Lake, nearby).  1st Street is a narrow street that crosses Main Street at the South end of Downtown.  When you find 1st Street, turn towards the lake.  Go down the hill and you will see a tall office building.  It is on the first floor of this building.  Note that these are gendered bathrooms in a small town, so I suggest using the one of the gender you are presenting as.

name: Simmons College
directions: there are numerous bathrooms that are single looking rooms that outside post male/female and disabled as the door sign.
comment: Should be a student, but the MCB is open to everyone and as long as you pretend to know what you're doing, no one should hassle you.

name: 227 Dedham Street
directions: Just walk up the ramp in the front of the building, go straight through the glass lobby doors and the bathrooms are right there clearly marked.
comment: The bathrooms are usually open from 9 am till around 6 PM Monday through Friday and occasionally open shorter hours on Saturday and closed on Sunday.

name: encuentro 5
directions: 5th floor
comment: Bathrooms are gendered. Two stalls in mens room, one you can't flush any paper or poop and the other doesn't lock. They are also fundraising to build an accessible bathroom and ramp.

name: Paper Moon Diner
directions: The rest room on the first floor (not downstairs next to the office) is gender neutral.
comment: The door to the gender-neutral restroom locks behind you.  The entire ground floor is accessible to people with disabilities.  The hallway leading to the dining area adjacent to this restroom may be a bit narrow for all wheelchairs.  The Paper Moon is also open 24 hours a day, and closed only a couple days a year.  I dig this place; they even have a couple vegan dishes, if you're looking for that option.

name: Dandelion Communitea Cafe
comment: Tuesday- Thursday:11am to 9pmUntil Sept 1st,After Sept 1st:Tuesday - Sunday11am to 11pmCLOSED MONDAYS

name: Ridgway Town Park
street: Corners of Lena and Charles st.
comment: Gendered 2 seater bathrooms. Stalls have good locks and Main doors have deadbolts that can be turned from inside. Not very busy bathrooms so it's not to hard to get them to yourself. Also they are very clean and nice. They are locked after dark due to a history of some vandalism.

name: Conoco Gas Station
directions: Go back past the drink coolers (Straight ahead from one set of doors, to the left from the other) Turn right into the hallway. There are two gendered bathrooms each a one seater with a lock.

name: Texaco Gas Station
directions: On the far wall there are two doors. The 'women's' is the closer one the 'men's' is the one back by the drink coolers.
comment: Single seater and not to hard to slip in and out of relativly unobtrusivly.

name: Lupitas Bizarre Bazaar
directions: Walk straight back when you go in until you are in the kitchen section. Turn right. It's in the corner.

name: Ridgway true value hardware
directions: To the right and slightly behind the check out. Just to the left of the coffee pot.

name: Cimarron Books and Coffee
directions: Go in the front door and head for the left end of the coffee counter. This corner is full of Music and t-shirts. Open the door that is covered in pictures. This is the Bathroom.
comment: Good coffee, Fun to hang out in as long as the owner isn't there (She's just not as much fun) Good coffee (Again as long as the owner isn't the one making the coffee) A good place for political activism / Anti-bush type stuff. Lots of fun local area books. And a wonderful Cat named Willa Cather and yes she is allowed to go out.

name: supperclub
directions: single stall, locking genderfree bathroom rigfht next to the gendered bathrooms in the first room after the lobby.
comment: This venue is terrible and you should probably avoid it if you are not fond of Marina yuppies, str8 dudes who take up too much space, and rude service and ridiculously priced food and drinks. However, if you find yourself there for a completely random special event, the joy of your evening will be the fact that you can pee in peace. The bathroom, in fact, was even safer than the dance floor!

name: nervous dog coffee
directions: right by the counter
comment: rad little coffee shop with very friendly employees

name: J. M. Smith Hall University of Memphis
directions: The 2nd floor. It's near room 220, I remember.
comment: It's mostly a handicapped bathroom, but it has a man symbol and a woman symbol with a line between them on the bathroom door

name: Yale Divinity School
directions: First floor by the vending machines.
comment: Building is open to the public most of the day, Yale students 24/7.

name: East Quad
directions: directly inside main entrance.

name: AMC Loews Theatres - Alderwood Mall 16‎ -
directions: There are 2 locking genderfree or family restrooms, one on the left and one on the right side of the theater.
comment: Must have purchased a movie ticket to use the restrooms as they are behind the ticket line.

name: arturo's underground cafe
directions: ask to use the bathroom...it's through the kitchen
comment: open 7-2:30 on weekdays and 9-1 on saturdays

name: metro center mall
directions: east entrance by ruby tuesday and harkin theatre, left through food court.
comment: unisex family bathroom

name: Hamburger Mary's
directions: In the back of the restaurant, to the left.
comment: This is a gay-oriented restaurant/bar. Great food and drinks, and friendly staff. I go there fairly regularly.

name: Target
directions: This restroom is adjacent to the pharmacy
comment: One toilet in this room and the door locks

name: Walmart
directions: There are bathrooms in the back, by the arts and crafts department.  There is a handicap bathroom that is large and locks.

name: Pel' Meni
directions: All the way back, through the back door of the main room. When you get to the back wall of the building take a right
comment: Open til 3am. Good cheap food: menu consists of Russian dumplings: potato or meat. That's all!

name: Kitty Cat Klub
directions: Downstairs (lots of stairs!)
comment: Everyone pees together here--multi-stall, genderfree bathroom. Cutest Bar in Minneapolis, and pretty queer friendly.

name: Kirby Student Center
directions: Two accessible gender-neutral restrooms in Multicultural Center Staff office area. Restrooms are 225 C and 225 D. Both rooms require keys. If you are in a student organization in the Multicultural Center, the office key will open both restrooms. Please lock from inside.

name: UMD Kirby Plaza
directions: Restrooms: 245G and F, 304 and 303A.

name: Bagley Classroom
directions: Two Unisex Restrooms, Room 103 and 104.

name: La Note
directions: In the back, up a few stairs
comment: It's usually very busy, so it would be easy to sneak in unnoticed--2 genderfree bathrooms--queer friendly restaurant--great pancakes!

name: La Mediterranee
directions: All the way in the back, past the kitchen

name: Cafe Van Kleef
directions: All the way in the back
comment: On weekends there's a small cover, and there can be a long line since there's only one toilet in the whole place, but it's a cute bar!

name: Crepevine
directions: genderfree bathroom on upper and lower floor
comment: Good crepes, too!

name: Cesar
directions: All the way in the back past the bar
comment: A litle upscale, but nice genderfree bathrooms

name: Public bathroom on street
directions: Near the BART entrance.
comment: Never used one of these.

name: Carmike 12
directions: In the back right of the building by the exit close to the last theaters.

name: Taqueria Pancho Villa
directions: Stick to the left wall and proceed to the back of the restaurant.
comment: Dirty bathroom.

name: Sebhali Cafe
directions: You must pass through the cafe (which is inconspicuous from the street since there is a florist hiding the entrance) and through the glass door at the back to reach the bathrooms.

name: Starbucks
directions: The bathroom is in the back right corner of the cafe. When you walk in the door, look straight ahead and you'll find it.
comment: Not the cleanest bathroom, but oh well.

name: Redbones Barbecue
directions: There are 2 downstairs that are ungendered, go right down the stairs and hang a left, hug the left wall. They have some weird figures painted on the doors. Both single, locking rooms.
comment: Great funky barbecue place in Davis Sq! If downstairs is closed for dining access may be more difficult... but it's definitely open and crowded in the evenings.

name: Gargoyles on the Square
directions: In back on right through the dining room
comment: Both restrooms are marked "party" in rhinestones! Nice fancy bar and fine dining, friendly.

name: Yale Art Center
directions: It's an art gallery.Back of gallery is a single bathroom.
comment: Monday, Wednesday, and Friday 1:00PM to 6:00PM and Saturday 11:00AM to 3:00PM

name: La Montanita Coop
directions: Back behind the produce.

name: Flying Star
directions: Bathroom are back and to the right - near the coffee and hot water station.

name: Harwood Art Center
directions: This is an Art center in an old school.Take front hallway to left (after front office) and enter doorway on right. Room with bulletin boards, vending machines and a single bathroom.

name: Speedway Gas Station
directions: Turn left when walking through the opening doors.
comment: Kinda scuzzy sometimes, but hey, it's the only one in town.

name: Satellite Coffee
directions: Back of coffee shop.
comment: Get key from espresso bar.

name: Flying Goat Cafe
directions: Off the town sqaure.  Walk in, it's on the left.  Single potty, lockable bathroom.  Cool staff.
comment: Good info on BB about local events.

name: Bukowski\\
directions: Back of building
comment: Two gendered bathrooms and one \\\"handicapped\\\", all single-stall and locking

name: Gino's Pizzeria
directions: walk around the counter, it should be easy to find.
comment: I haven't been in this bathroom, but I've heard it's one you only use if you really have to. They're open until 1:45 am.

name: Sammy's Pizzeria
directions: If you walk into the back section it's on your left, green door.
comment: You should buy food if you want to use it, they say it's for customers only. They're open until (I think) 3 am.

name: Stella's
street: corner of College Ave. and Dryden Ave. (in Collegetown)
directions: They have a men's room, a women's room, and an 'other' bathroom. I haven't been there, but friends told me that it's one to add here.
comment: it's a bar, so you may be carded at the door, but other than that you can go right into the restroom.

name: Collegetown Bagels (Aurora St. location)
street: corner of Aurora St. and Seneca St.
directions: If you walk in the door leading to the dining area, it's straight back past the swinging doors (on the left).
comment: they're open as early as 6:30 am. I'm not sure of the summer hours, but winter hours are until 7 pm on weekdays and saturdays and until 4 on sundays.

name: Himawari
directions: Back right corner of the restaurant.
comment: This bathroom was spotless and odorless. What a nice experience. Stop in and have a glass of sake or a sushi roll and enjoy this unisex bathroom.

directions: In the back past the register.  It's on the street level, but not so wheelchair accessible because the door entry way is small.
comment: I've heard them say "for customers only," but it just depends who is working.  Usually they're cool about it.7am till 9pm 7days a week.Free wireless for laptops.  Laundry next door.http://www.cafepetra.biz/

name: Atlas Cafe
directions: There are two genderfree single-stall bathrooms with locking doors and their own sinks in the cafe.  One is on the left past the long counter, the other off of the back patio.
comment: http://www.atlascafe.net/  It's easier to stroll in and out when it is busy, which it often is.

name: Arc Cafe
directions: On the main floor with wheelchair-accessible ramp.  Enter cafe, restroom is past counter on left.

name: Gregory Hall / UIUC
directions: Basement and fourth floor
comment: Building hours: 7 a.m. to midnight weekdays, 10:30 p.m. weekends during fall and spring semesters; 8 to 5 p.m. weekdays other times

name: Lawrence University - Memorial Hall
directions: Entry level floor, across from gendered restrooms
comment: Academic building during the day so fairly quiet during the day.  Basement of building hosts on campus bar which means it is open longer than many other academic buildings

name: Richard Hugo House
directions: Two gender neutral bathrooms - one facing the coffee counter and the other behind it
comment: In Capitol Hill, Seattle's gay district and Hugo House is a landmark close to all the bars and action. You can get coffee at almost all times when its open and you just drop in a suggested donation of I think a $1.50

name: Washington Stae Ferries
directions: In the passenger deck on one side and in the center and often close to one of the staircases leading to the parked cars below
comment: The washington state ferries have a family bathroom that is gender neutral and is for a single person (or one with kids) and lockable. I have used one while going from Seattle to Bremerton enroute to Port Angeles all dressed up

name: Mothers Restaurant
directions: In back of restaurant.
comment: Gay friendly town but weekends are very touristy

name: Eastfield Mall, MA
street: Eastfield Mall food court, Springfield, MA
directions: Food court, next to security, new addition to building, 'Family Room'
comment: Next to Ladies and Mens rooms

name: Cafe Asia
comment: Cafe Asia is an achingly hip pan-Asian restaurant with great sushi.  The downtown location has a bunch of idividual bathroom stalls with a large, communal sink in the general restroom area.  See: http://www.cafeasia.com/index.html

name: Brass Mill Center
directions: Second level, next to the food court there is a family rest room next to the men's and women's rest rooms

name: State Park
directions: Outside the museum of Natural History in Morrow Park

name: McDonalds
directions: Walk right into the back, there is a Women's, a Genderfree Handicap Accessible, and a Men's.
comment: While the restaurant drive thru is open 24/7/365 the lobby is open 6am to 10pm only.  The staff seems to be gender curious but otherwise don't really care one way or another.  I transitioned and over the years they never said a word, though ironically I was recently asked if I know where any local lesbian clubs because more often than not my sister-in-law is in with me.

name: Santa Clara Central Park
directions: near pavillion
comment: What a Godperson send you are!
